			<div class="commentcount">292</div>

				<p>Good cake. I made it cutting down the sugar to 150 gr + 2 tbsp on top.<br />
 + 240 g plain flour, of which half was fine cornmeal flour (in Italy it is called Fioretto, the finest corn flour basically). I coated the cake tin (23 cm) with butter and coarse polenta flour. I did not have any thyme, otherwise that would have gone into the cake too.<br />
I have also added the zest of 1 lemon. I make something similar also using rasberries.<br />
I am now playing with the idea of using half light olive oil+half veg oil.</p>
<p>excellent blog. u r doing a really good work<br />
ciao from Milano<br />
stefano<br />
ps: the American cup sistem very confusing,I found charts with different conversions (cups to grams). I now resort to scoop and level and then weight all my ingredients, when using American recipe. I have found that 1 cup plain flour is between 150/160 gr</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
