<p>I used a 10-inch springform, buttered and floured (just to make sure there&#8217;d be no sticking). I also cooked it the full 60 minutes at 325F (70 minutes total). It puffed up quite nicely, and was perfectly golden on the edges.</p>
<p>You&#8217;re right, though, Deb &#8211; I think it&#8217;s just a tiny smidgeon too sweet. I&#8217;m going to try this again next weekend with 2 tablespoons less sugar. (I honestly think the sugar on top would make up for those two tablespoons perfectly.)</p>
