				<p>I made this twice over the weekend. One on Saturday (to test it) and one for a party on Sunday.  I used 1/2 almond meal and 1/2 all purpose flour, and low-fat milk (what we had), and it tasted absolutely delicious.  The only issue was that the strawberries sunk below and were entirely invisible on the top.  I didn&#8217;t layer them the first time, so on the second time, I layered many of them (to make them higher).  They still sunk below.  We used a 9 in deep dish pie plate- very similar to yours.  So, I&#8217;m not sure if it was the flour or the milk- or both&#8230; but I&#8217;d like to keep trying  so that the strawberries stay on the top!</p>
