<li class="commentbody highlighted" id="comment-1784048">
			<cite><a href='http://smittenkitchen.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>deb</a></cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-1784048" title="">April 16, 2012</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">693</div>

				<p>Let&#8217;s see&#8230; a deep-dish 9-inch pie plate like what I used here holds about 8 cups batter. An 8-inch cake pan holds about 4 cups so you might even want to halve it. That said, the batter didn&#8217;t make it to the top of this pan so you might just need to 1 1/3 it. Hope that helps.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
